( 2, 'honsfeld05', 9, '2 of the anti tank guns of 612th Tank Destroyer Battalion. 1 of the Surviving members, sgt Bryant tells the story: I was standing guard at front door when I saw German Paratroops infiltrating the town. I woke up my crew and got our 3-inch gun unhooked from the half-track and setup. At first it was only infantry and the germans had taken cover behind the barn some 80m away from our positions, we quickly shot at point blank range into the barn. We heard cries and body part, hay and wood flew everywhere. Every time I fired the gun, I had to jump up on the rail to keep it from kicking back from the recoil, because of the frozen soil. The second gun crew was also trying to get their gun in position, but it was too late. As a tank got from behind the barn, its sprayed machine gun fire and killed 5 members of the crews. I was shot through the hand and the shoulder. I managed to get away with some other survivors but it would not be long before we needed to surrender to the Germans.', '50.38236618', '6.27816391', 'Honssfeld', 1, '1944-12-01', 1, '', 1, '2021-02-14 15:39:12', '2017-08-07 17:39:23'),
