( 1, 'lagleize01', 9, 'In the city of La Gleize, 2 tanks were left by the Germans. A Panther (on the left of the soldiers) was left in a street next to the church and  the King Tiger (in the back of the picture) was left in the Rue de L Église. On January 18, 1945, men of the 82nd Airborne Reconnaissance Platoon decided to test the impenetrability of the King Tiger. The weapons chosen for the competition were the Bazooka vs. the Panzerschreck. The armor on the Tiger II its glacis is 150mm - about 15cm. Both guns only penetrated to a depth of 10 cm, although this was enough to pass through the 80mm armor plate on the side of the turret.', '50.41129303', '5.84706640', 'La Gleize', 1, '1945-01-18', 1, '', 1, '2020-12-05 20:43:30', '2019-01-27 19:48:50'),
