( 1, 'maasMechelenIncident01', 10, 'Wreckage of the Messerschmitt Bf.108, flown by Major Erich Hoenmanns and Major Helmut Reinberger after they had to make an imergancy landing in Maas-Mechelen.\r\nDuring the Phoney War on January 10 at around 11.30, a German plane with plans for Fall Gelb, the German attack on the Low Countries, made an emergency landing in neutral Belgium. When the 2 officers realized that they mistook the Meuse for the Rhine and therefore were not in Germany, hastily tried to burn the documents. Meanwhile, men from the border guard came to the crash side and captured the 2 officers. During their interrogation, there was a second attempt to destroy the documents, which led to suspicion by the Belgian investigators and turning the documents over to the secret service. The documents describe plans for paradrops in and around Namur to lay siege to the bridges in an upcoming operation. It would have been one of the major mistakes that ultimately led to the postponement of Fall Gelb, the attack on the low countries and the outbreak of World War II in the west till May 1940.', '50.97283554', '5.71566248', 'Maasmechelen', 1, '1940-01-13', 1, 'More info: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mechelen_incident', 1, '2020-11-29 12:49:43', '2019-01-27 20:08:46'),
