( 1, 'laRoche02', 9, 'Soldiers of the British 51st Highland Division and soldiers of the American C-Company 635th Tank destroyer battalion meet in La Roche. Private Harris McAllister shared the following about the photo: The photo was taken after the battle of La Roche. We crossed the destroyed bridge over the Ourthe river and ran into the Americans in their armored car. We sat in front of a garage, around a kerosene fire in a bucket and drank a cup of coffee they offered us. At that point, the photographer arrived in a jeep, along with a reporter. Realizing we were in different uniforms and that this was the regrouping. He then asked if we could meet each other on the corner of Rue de la Gare and Rue de Ceille. We did and it gave him the opportunity to take a more suitable photo.', '50.18382263', '5.57649326', 'La Roche', 1, '1945-01-11', 1, '', 1, '2021-02-09 20:16:53', '2020-09-01 16:32:45'),
