( 2, 'hotton06', 1, 'On May 11th around 9:20 am, the Belgian 1st company of the 25th engineer battalion blew up the bridge over the Ourthe in Hotton. The steel frame broke in two places and collapsed. But because the shallow river bed on that side of the river, light cargo and infantry could still cross the bridge without getting their feet wet. The French Lieutenant Queverue, of the French Engineers 33/1, gave the order to completely destroy the bridge. Around noon the bridge a second attempt was made. But again it was not completely destroyed. So at 13:35 a 3rd attempt was made. The dust of the advancing German 5th Panzer Division was already visible, causing the engineers to leave as quick as possible. As can be seen in the photo, also this was unfortunately not enough to completely destroy the bridge.', '50.26812363', '5.44593191', 'Hotton', 1, '1940-04-11', 1, '', 1, '2020-11-29 18:16:23', '2020-11-18 17:23:01'),
