( 1, 'vlissingen03', 16, 'On the night of November 1 to 2, the 7th/9th Battalion Royal Scots, commanded by Lt. Col. Michael E. Melville, were ordered to take the Grand Hotel Britannia. The hotel was the headquarters \"Verteidigungsbereich Vlissingen\" of Kommandeur Oberst Eugen Reinhardt. The attack was launched at 03.30 hours, but it would take until 04.15 hours before the first bunker was attacked. A 20mm cannon on the roof of the Hotel made progress to the Hotel very slow, as did the many trenches, barbed wire and other barriers. Lt.Col. Melville was injured while taking a pulse on his men. Command was taken over by Major Hugh Rose. Encouraged by the wounded Melville, the men opened, shouting \"On the Royals!\" and attack with renewed courage.', '51.44941663', '3.55988652', 'Vlissingen', 3, '1944-11-04', 1, '', 1, '2021-08-21 21:13:12', '2021-08-21 10:05:25'),
