( 1, 'amsterdam05', 16, 'Dutch civilians who became victem to German bullets on the 7th of May during the Dam square shooting are placed next to the church.\nWhile the formal surrender of the German troops was already signed in Wageningen on the 5th of May, some parts of the Netherlands were still under German control. On the 7th of May, as Canadian Troops entered the City, dutch Forces of the interiar aready begun, disarming the German troops. A German soldier who refused was shot, which probably was the reason why the shooting at Dam Square started.', '52.37352940', '4.89237070', 'Amsterdam', 3, '1945-05-07', 1, '', 1, '2022-03-31 22:32:18', '2022-03-27 17:39:03'),
